# The `PMDataManager` Class Reference

<DoxygenPage pluginConfig={pluginConfig}>

<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/pmdatamanager">PMDataManager</a> provides the common place to manage the analysis data used by pass managers. <a href="#details">More...</a>

## Description {#details}

<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/pmdatamanager">PMDataManager</a> provides the common place to manage the analysis data used by pass managers.

### emitInstrCountChangedRemark() {#ab3115ef36979b45874f244f374e79d98}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>void PMDataManager::emitInstrCountChangedRemark (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/pass">Pass</a> &#42; P, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/module">Module</a> &amp; M, int64&#95;t Delta, unsigned CountBefore, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/stringmap">StringMap</a>&lt; std::pair&lt; unsigned, unsigned &gt; &gt; &amp; FunctionToInstrCount, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/function">Function</a> &#42; F=nullptr)</>}>
Emit a remark signifying that the number of IR instructions in the module changed.

<code>F</code> is optionally passed by passes which run on Functions, and thus always know whether or not a non-empty function is available.

<code>FunctionToInstrCount</code> maps the name of a <code><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/function">Function</a></code> to a pair. The first member of the pair is the IR count of the <code><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/function">Function</a></code> before running <code>P</code>, and the second member is the IR count of the <code><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/function">Function</a></code> after running <code>P</code>.
